history.content:
Edit: this is what I received: 

Hello Sarah,
 
Thank you for contact the SIS Production Support Team. As of July 18th when a student receives time conflict error message, a notification is generated and surfaces on their CalCentral dashboard. Students then use the message to request a Time Conflict override. If no other restrictions prevent students from enrolling in both classes (such as exceeding Phase unit limits, closed class, etc) the time conflict restriction will be waived and their enrollment will be processed. For more information about the enrollment time conflict process, please see - http://sis.berkeley.edu/time-conflict
 
Please advise if you have any additional questions.
 
Let me know if there are follow up questions.
Thanks,
Sarah
It should have popped up when you tried to register, but I am hearing reports that it might not be there anymore. Emailing SIS right now to see where it may have gone. Stay tuned.

children.subject: Not necessarily. I think they are overwhelmed with many requests and it's taking longer than they anticipated to process. I would keep checking in with them.
I have waited several days for my time conflict override request to be processed. However, when I submitted the form, it said to check back the following day. Does this mean my request was denied?
I would try submitting a conflict override form just in case you are being prevented from enrolling in CS 186 but don't know it.
I have been unable to locate this form. Would you be able to point it out or link it to me?

I placed CS 186 on the waitlist expecting to get a conflict notification, since its lecture time conflicts with one of the EE 16A midterms. However, it seemed to waitlist without any conflict and I did not get such a notification. Should I look into this or just assume that I have been successfully placed on the waitlist?
